# Install SystemC

Get SystemC from here [accellera.org](https://www.accellera.org/downloads/standards/systemc)

Extract

```sh
cd systemc-2.3.3
./configure --prefix=$(pwd)/../systemcinstall 'CXXFLAGS=-std=c++11'
make
make check
make install
```
It will install systemc on a folder named systemcinstall at the same level of the current directory

# Install ArchC

Get Arch from github
```sh
git clone https://github.com/ArchC/ArchC.git
```
Dependecies : bison flex libdw-dev autoconf libtool autoreconf make gcc

```sh
cd Archc
./autogen.sh
INSTALLDIR=$(pwd)/../acinstall
SYSTEMCPATH=$(pwd)/../systemcinstall
./configure --prefix=$INSTALLDIR --with-systemc=$SYSTEMCPATH 'CXXFLAGS=-std=c++11'
make 
make install
```

# Configure PATH environment

In the Archc folder:
```sh
source env.sh
```

You can also copy PATH variable to .bashrc
You can also add this line for future use of systemc
```sh
export SYSTEMC_HOME=PATH_TO/systemcinstall
```

Ensure everything is OK

```sh
acsim -h
```

# Compiling simulator

```sh
acsim msp430x.ac -noabi
```
**Warning**
```sh
acsim msp430x.ac -noabi
```
might change the MAKEFILE, checkout the MAKEFILE from the repo after the command

```sh
make
```